text_context: wacac is pleased to host college fairs in california and nevada for high school students, their parents, and high school counselors. all of wacacs fairs are free to attend and include free parking. we typically welcome representatives from more than 100 institutions at our events!
label: Other

text_context: prior to attending a wacac college fair, students and parents can register using a special link to receive an event barcode.
label: Other

text_context: after registering, youll get a reminder with your personal barcode two hours before the fair.
label: Other

text_context: at the fair, show your barcode to colleges. theyll scan it to get your information.
label: Other

text_context: , youll get a report with information about all of the colleges that scanned your barcode. youll also start receiving information directly from the colleges about the application process, financial aid, and important deadlines.
label: Other

text_context: wacac college fair exhibitors play a major role in the success of each of our programs. the of the western association for college admission counseling, along with members of the local planning committee are responsible for creating a professional and safe environment for the delivery of wacacs college fair program.
label: Other

text_context: wacac college fair exhibitor rules and regulations:
label: Other

text_context: our college fairs are for two- and four-year colleges and universities that are regionally accredited. on a space-available basis, we may accommodate some non-profit organizational members who assist students with the transition from high school to college. wacac reserves the right to refuse the registration of any institution or organization. independent counselors and/or educational consultants are not eligible. non-profits who would like to exhibit, should reach out to the college fair chair before registering to see if accommodations can be made.
label: Other

text_context: representatives must present clear and accurate information concerning their institution or agency while avoiding ambiguous, questionable, or false information about competing institutions and agencies.
label: Other

text_context: only full-time admissions officers, institutional representatives, delegated salaried school officials, or trained alumni shall represent schools or agencies during wacac programs. use of current students or recruits during wacac fairs will not be allowed.
label: Other
